<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                                <head>No. 38.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lieut. <persName type="from">Young</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blount</persName></hi>.</head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Honolulu, Hawaiian Islands</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16, 1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: During the day of the 17th of
                                    January, 1893, at Arion Hall I was in command of the
                                    artillery.</p>
                                <p>Capt. Wiltse said to me: “I will not allow any fighting in the
                                    city.”</p>
                                <p>Very respectfully yours,</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lucien Young</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lieutenant, U. S.
                                    Navy.</hi></signed></closer>
                                <postscript>
                                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">J. H. Blount</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu, Hawaiian Islands.</hi></p>
                                </postscript>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>